# Testing and verification — terminal use

## Quality gate (the **default** chained verification)

When running the full **quality gate** — ESLint, TypeScript check, Stylelint, and Vitest with coverage (**100%** on all four v8 metrics for **`src-electron`** and **`helpers`**, **100%** on all four for renderer **`src`** **`.ts`** in **`unit-src-renderer`**, **100%** statements, functions, and lines for **`.ts`** under **`src/components`**, **`src/layouts`**, and **`src/pages`** in **`unit-components`**, **`.vue`** SFCs reported with **60%** watermarks only) — use **one** terminal invocation. Prefer the **`yarn testbatch:verify`** script in `package.json` (same steps, stops on the first failure):

`yarn testbatch:verify`

**Yarn 1.x**: do **not** use `yarn check` for this — it is a built-in that validates the dependency tree, not this script.

Equivalent explicit chain (for context or copy-paste without the script): `yarn lint:eslint && yarn lint:typescript && yarn lint:stylelint && yarn test:coverage:verify`

For a **faster** unit pass without coverage instrumentation, run **`yarn test:unit`** (Vitest workspace: electron, **`src`** TS, helpers, components) while iterating; finish with **`yarn testbatch:verify`** before commits.

**Exception**: if you are **debugging** a specific failing step, run that command **alone** (and any narrower follow-ups) until it passes, then re-run the full chained gate before commit or changelog edits.

By default, do not extend this chain with `yarn quasar:build:electron`, Playwright, or Storybook.

## Full-suite gates (`testbatch:ensure:nochange` / `testbatch:ensure:change`)

When you explicitly need the full project gate in one command, use one of:

- **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** — `testbatch:verify`, **`yarn quasar:build:electron:summarized`** (captures Quasar/electron-builder output; on success prints one line; on failure dumps the full log—by default written under **`test-results/quasar-build-electron-last.log`**, gitignored with **`test-results/`**), Playwright component + E2E, **`yarn test:storybook:smoke`**, then **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** (compare committed Storybook VRT snapshots; fails on drift).
- **`yarn testbatch:ensure:change`** — same chain through E2E and smoke, then **`yarn test:storybook:visual:update`** to refresh Storybook VRT baselines. Use only when intentional UI changes are approved and you will commit the updated snapshots.

Treat these as the intentional exception to the isolation rule. **Do not** run **`testbatch:ensure:change`** in CI or to validate an unchanged baseline.

The default **GitHub Actions** **Verify** workflow (`.github/workflows/verify.yml`) runs **`yarn testbatch:verify`** only — not Storybook smoke/visual, Electron production build, or Playwright component/E2E. Run **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** / **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** locally when you need VRT.

## Everything else — one command per terminal

Run each of these in its **own** terminal invocation (do not chain them with each other or with the quality gate in the same line) unless you are intentionally running **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** or **`yarn testbatch:ensure:change`**:

- `yarn quasar:build:electron` (full build log to the terminal; use when you want streaming output)
- `yarn test:components`
- `yarn test:e2e`
- `yarn test:storybook:smoke`
- `yarn test:storybook:visual` / `yarn test:storybook:visual:update` (and other `test:storybook:visual*` variants)

Keep logs isolated for readability and easier failure triage.

**Playwright Electron `userData`:** Component and E2E runs set `TEST_ENV`; the main process then uses **`%APPDATA%/<package.json name>/playwright-user-data`** (this repo: **`Roaming\fantasia-archive\playwright-user-data`**), **not** **`fantasia-archive-dev`**. Specs call **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData()`** in **`test.beforeEach`** (**`helpers/playwrightHelpers/playwrightUserDataReset.ts`**) so that tree is deleted before each test. See **`src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/fixAppName.ts`**, **`src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts`**, and [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc).

## Reporting

When reporting progress, list results in execution order (for the quality gate, you may report one combined pass/fail, or break out the first failing step if the chain stopped early).

## Local types extraction rule

- For Vue (`.vue`) and TypeScript (`.ts`) source files, move small file-local interfaces/type aliases into a colocated `<filename>.types.ts` file and import them back.
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
